Description: 
Reporter Mark Sparrow describes the poor quality of 
meals he received during a 10-week stay in an NHS 
hospital, and sets out to discover whether his experience 
was a one-off or symptomatic of a deeper problem. He 
meets young cystic fibrosis patients whose parents take 
them out of hospital to local pubs and restaurants for their
meals, and talks to the relatives of elderly people who 
claim their loved ones have been served substandard 
food and then given no help to consume it.
